IMPORTANT NOTE
Be sure to store generated secret keys, passwords, and tokens securely. Do not commit sensitive credentials to the public repository.
Validation functions are available and recommended for checking the strength of credentials before deploying in a production environment.
This library is under continuous development; please check the changelog for information on version changes, bug fixes, or new features.
The minimum Node.js version is 24; ensure your runtime environment is compatible.
